==English==

[[image:C-Falter Polygonia C-album.jpg|thumb|A butterfly]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[buttorfleoge]]'', corresponding to ''[[butter]]'' + ''[[fly]]'', perhaps with reference to the colour of certain species including the [[Wikipedia:Brimstone (butterfly)|brimstone butterfly]], ''Gonepteryx rhamni''.  Compare German ''[[Schmetterling]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* (''US'') {{IPA|/ˈbʌtɝflaɪ/}}, (''UK'') {{IPA|/ˈbʌtəflaɪ/}}
{{audio|en-ca-butterfly.ogg|Audio (CA)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|butterflies}}

# {{insect}} A flying [[insect]] of the [[order]] ''[[Lepidoptera]]'', distinguished from moths by their [[diurnal]] activity and generally brighter colouring.
# A [[swimming]] [[stroke]] in which the body is [[prone]], the arms are moved in [[simultaneous]] circles, and the feet are kicked up and down.
# A use of surgical tape, cut into thin strips and placed across an open wound to hold it closed.
#: '''''butterfly''' tape''

